<div id="review_3842387739" class="review" itemprop="reviews" itemscope itemtype="http://schema.org/Review">
  <link itemprop="url" href="https://www.goodreads.com/review/show/3842387739" />
    <a title="Theodore Knight" class="left imgcol" href="/user/show/48055913-theodore-knight"><img alt="Theodore Knight" src="https://images.gr-assets.com/users/1445230025p2/48055913.jpg" /></a>

  <div class="left bodycol">
    <div class="reviewHeader uitext stacked">
        <a class="reviewDate createdAt right" href="/review/show/3842387739?book_show_action=true">Mar 13, 2021</a>

      <span itemprop="author" itemscope itemtype="http://schema.org/Person">
        <a title="Theodore Knight" class="user" itemprop="url" name="Theodore Knight" href="/user/show/48055913-theodore-knight">Theodore Knight</a>
      </span>

        rated it
        <span class=" staticStars notranslate" title="it was amazing"><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10">it was amazing</span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span></span>

          <span class="greyText">&nbsp;&middot;&nbsp;</span>
          <a class="lightGreyText" title="Paperback 9780375726156" href="/book/show/89272.John_Brown_Abolitionist">review of another edition</a>


        

    </div>


        <div class="reviewText stacked">
              <span id="reviewTextContainer3842387739" class="readable"
              >
            
<span id="freeTextContainer11075922738195263226">A must read for an infusion of forgotten history. My memory from what I was taught in school was John Brown was crazy and what he did was of marginal significance. After reading this book his life went from obscure in history to the elevated position of a relevant significant historical hero. On par with Lincoln and others of that time. His impact on history is notable for what he did in spearheading a nation&apos;s attention to confront the question of the wrong of enslaving humans. The impact of it</span>
  <span id="freeText11075922738195263226" style="display:none">A must read for an infusion of forgotten history. My memory from what I was taught in school was John Brown was crazy and what he did was of marginal significance. After reading this book his life went from obscure in history to the elevated position of a relevant significant historical hero. On par with Lincoln and others of that time. His impact on history is notable for what he did in spearheading a nation's attention to confront the question of the wrong of enslaving humans. The impact of it should be given priority in teaching our nation's history. This book opened a total respect for the cause this great man was willing to die for. Please carefully consider adding this work to your library.</span>
  <a data-text-id="11075922738195263226" href="#" onclick="swapContent($(this));; return false;">...more</a>

