<div class='bookAuthorProfile__about'>

<span id="freeTextContainer1926032369371504826"><strong>David S. Reynolds</strong> is a Distinguished Professor of English and American Studies at the City University of New York. His works include the award-winning <em>Waking Giant: America in the Age of Jackson</em>, <em>Walt Whitman&apos;s America</em>, and <em>John Brown, Abolitionist</em>. He lives on Long Island in New York.</span>
  <span id="freeText1926032369371504826" style="display:none"><strong>David S. Reynolds</strong> is a Distinguished Professor of English and American Studies at the City University of New York. His works include the award-winning <em>Waking Giant: America in the Age of Jackson</em>, <em>Walt Whitman's America</em>, and <em>John Brown, Abolitionist</em>. He lives on Long Island in New York.</span>
